7. Input-file interface
--------------------------------------------------------------------------------

The gridless branch is configured through the same AMPS parameter file parsed by:

  util/amps_param_parser.h
  util/amps_param_parser.cpp

The minimum sections needed for a typical run are:

  #CALCULATION_MODE
      CALC_TARGET       CUTOFF_RIGIDITY | DENSITY_SPECTRUM
      FIELD_EVAL_METHOD GRIDLESS

  #PARTICLE_SPECIES
      species charge and mass

  #BACKGROUND_FIELD
      FIELD_MODEL, epoch, and model-specific drivers

  #DOMAIN_BOUNDARY
      outer box and R_INNER

  #OUTPUT_DOMAIN
      POINTS or SHELLS definition

  #NUMERICAL
      DT_TRACE, MAX_STEPS, MAX_TRACE_TIME, etc.

For cutoff runs add:

  #CUTOFF_RIGIDITY

For density/spectrum runs add:

  #DENSITY_SPECTRUM
  #SPECTRUM

Optional sections:

  #BOUNDARY_ANISOTROPY   (for DS_BOUNDARY_MODE = ANISOTROPIC)
  #ENERGY_CHANNELS       (extra integral-flux channels)

IMPORTANT INPUT CONVENTION:

  The gridless solvers trace in GSM. The parser stores coordinate labels but does
  not perform a full coordinate transformation of input points for the user.
  Input coordinates therefore need to be consistent with the solver’s GSM-based
  assumptions unless an external conversion has already been applied.

--------------------------------------------------------------------------------
8. Command-line interface
--------------------------------------------------------------------------------

Main usage:

  ./amps -h
  ./amps -mode gridless -i AMPS_PARAM.in
  ./amps -mode gridless -i AMPS_PARAM.in -mover BORIS
  ./amps -mode gridless -i AMPS_PARAM.in -density-mode ANISOTROPIC
  ./amps -mode gridless -i AMPS_PARAM.in -max-trace-distance 200

Useful options:

  -h | --help
      Print the solver help message.

  -mode <gridless|3d>
      Select execution path. This README documents the gridless branch only.

  -i <file>
      AMPS parameter file.

  -mover <BORIS|HC4|RK2|RK4|RK6|GC2|GC4|GC6|HYBRID>
      Override the default/shared mover.

      HC4 aliases accepted by the parser include HIGUERA_CARY4,
      HIGUERA-CARY4, HC_YOSHIDA4, BORIS4, and BORIS_YOSHIDA4.

  -density-mode <ISOTROPIC|ANISOTROPIC>
      Override DS_BOUNDARY_MODE for density/spectrum runs.

  -max-trace-distance <Re>
      Optional cumulative path-length cap in Earth radii.

For the authoritative CLI wording, see:

  util/cutoff_cli.cpp

